data.title: Eerste Divisie News and Features
data.meta_description: Get all the latest Eerste Divisie news, plus in-depth features and interviews. Keep up to-to-date with all Eerste Divisie news with FourFourTwo.com.
data.text:
Telstar tell rivals: Boozing in progress, no transfers please

Telstar have pleaded with other clubs not to take advantage of their state of inebriation after this week's Christmas drinks.

NAC agree Manchester City partnership

Dutch outfit NAC and Manchester City will be working closely together over the next five seasons after agreeing a formal partnership.

Eredivisie Play-offs: RKC Waawijk eye turnaround

RKC Waalwijk RKC Waalwijk host Excelsior in the second leg of their Eredivisie relegation play-off needing a stunning turnaround to stay in the division.

Eredivisie play-offs Review: Eagles relegated, NAC Breda earn reprieve

Go Ahead Eagles were consigned to relegation from the Eredivisie after losing their play-off 2-0 on aggregate to De Graafschap.

Nwakali leaves Arsenal for MVV loan spell

Kelechi Nwakali has joined Eerste Divisie side MVV from Arsenal on loan for the rest of the season.

Eredivisie Play-offs: AZ, Groningen eye Europe

Groningen AZ host Groningen in the first leg of their Eredivisie play-offs, with the two sides battling it out for a place in the UEFA Europa League.

Watch: Den Bosch's Danny Verbeek incredible open-goal miss from two yards out

In Other News... In the Dutch second tier, Verbeek missed an absolute sitter against Ajax II

Groningen reach Europe as Advocaat bows out

Groningen Groningen will feature in Europe for the first time since 2007 next season after beating AZ 3-0 in their play-off on Sunday.

Dutch side Den Bosch introduce 'pay per point' season ticket for next season

In Other News... The price of a season ticket at the Eerste Divisie club will be based on the team's performance next season.
